## 🟡 Règles STRONG

### STRONG-001 : Field avec description pour documentation

**Règle** : Utiliser Field(..., description="...") pour champs importants.

```python
# ✓ PRÉFÉRÉ
class EntityResponse(BaseModel):
    id: UUID = Field(..., description="Unique identifier")
    name: str = Field(..., description="Entity display name")
    status: str = Field(..., description="Current status: pending, active, completed")
    created_at: datetime = Field(..., description="Creation timestamp (ISO 8601)")
```

---

### STRONG-002 : Enums sérialisés en valeurs

**Règle** : Configurer Pydantic pour sérialiser enums en valeurs string.

```python
# ✓ PRÉFÉRÉ
from enum import Enum
from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict

class EntityStatus(str, Enum):
    PENDING = "pending"
    ACTIVE = "active"
    COMPLETED = "completed"

class EntityResponse(BaseModel):
    model_config = ConfigDict(use_enum_values=True)
    
    id: UUID
    status: EntityStatus  # Sérialisé en "pending", pas "EntityStatus.PENDING"

# JSON output
{"id": "...", "status": "pending"}  # ✓ String
```

---

### STRONG-003 : Champs optionnels avec None explicite

**Règle** : Les champs optionnels doivent avoir default=None explicite.

```python
# ✓ PRÉFÉRÉ
class EntityResponse(BaseModel):
    id: UUID
    name: str
    description: str | None = None          # ✓ Explicite
    metadata: dict | None = None            # ✓ Explicite
    parent_id: UUID | None = None           # ✓ Explicite

# ⚠ MOINS CLAIR
class EntityResponse(BaseModel):
    description: str | None  # Implicite mais moins clair
```

---

### STRONG-004 : Pas de nested list directement

**Règle** : Éviter listes imbriquées sans wrapper.

```python
# ✓ PRÉFÉRÉ
class OrderItemResponse(BaseModel):
    id: UUID
    name: str
    quantity: int

class OrderResponse(BaseModel):
    id: UUID
    total: Decimal
    items: list[OrderItemResponse]  # ✓ Liste d'objets typés

# ⚠ À ÉVITER
class OrderResponse(BaseModel):
    items: list[list[str]]  # ⚠ Liste de listes
    tags: list[dict]           # ⚠ Liste de dicts non typés
```

---

### STRONG-005 : Relations imbriquées limitées

**Règle** : Limiter la profondeur d'imbrication à 2-3 niveaux maximum.

```python
# ✓ PRÉFÉRÉ - 2 niveaux
class EntityResponse(BaseModel):
    id: UUID
    name: str
    owner: UserSummary  # ✓ 1 niveau

class UserSummary(BaseModel):
    id: UUID
    name: str
    # Pas de nested relations ici

# ⚠ À ÉVITER - >3 niveaux
class EntityResponse(BaseModel):
    owner: UserResponse
        organization: OrganizationResponse
            parent: OrganizationResponse
                creator: UserResponse  # ⚠ 4 niveaux
```

---

### STRONG-006 : Pagination structure standardisée

**Règle** : Utiliser une structure de pagination cohérente.

```python
# ✓ PRÉFÉRÉ
class PaginationMetadata(BaseModel):
    total: int = Field(..., description="Total items count")
    page: int = Field(..., ge=1, description="Current page (1-indexed)")
    page_size: int = Field(..., ge=1, le=200, description="Items per page")
    total_pages: int = Field(..., description="Total pages")
    has_more: bool = Field(..., description="Has next page")

class EntityListResponse(BaseModel):
    items: list[EntityResponse]
    pagination: PaginationMetadata

# Calcul total_pages
total_pages = (total + page_size - 1) // page_size  # Ceiling division
has_more = page < total_pages
```

