## 📋 Aide-mémoire

**Checklist réponses API** :

- [ ] BaseModel Pydantic (pas dict brut)
- [ ] Timestamps ISO 8601 avec json_encoders
- [ ] from_attributes=True pour ORM mapping
- [ ] Séparation Request/Response models
- [ ] Collections wrappées (pas liste nue)
- [ ] Field descriptions pour documentation
- [ ] use_enum_values=True pour enums
- [ ] Champs optionnels avec =None explicite
- [ ] Pagination structure standardisée
- [ ] Imbrication limitée (2-3 niveaux max)

**Template BaseModel standard** :

```python
from pydantic import BaseModel, ConfigDict, Field
from datetime import datetime
from uuid import UUID

class EntityResponse(BaseModel):
    """Response model for entity endpoints."""
    
    model_config = ConfigDict(
        from_attributes=True,
        use_enum_values=True,
        json_encoders={
            datetime: lambda v: v.isoformat() if v else None
        }
    )
    
    id: UUID = Field(..., description="Unique identifier")
    name: str = Field(..., description="Entity name")
    status: str = Field(..., description="Current status")
    created_at: datetime = Field(..., description="Creation timestamp")
    updated_at: datetime = Field(..., description="Last update timestamp")
```

